CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941, pg. 3 reads: "James Weldon Johnson Camp Model Project - Above are scenes from Camp James Weldon Johnson, situated on Raccoon Creek in foothills of the beautiful Allegehney [Allegheny] mountains just 34 miles from Pittsburg. Some of the children who enjoyed the facilities of the spacious grounds during the past two weeks are pictured...Scene in the spacious dining hall as a group of orderly youngsters dig i nat chow time.  note the happy expressions of the waiters..."
TitMainTitle: Girls, and boys, including one wearing striped shirt, walking with pitcher, eating at wooden tables and benches in dining hall at Camp Weldon Johnson, Beaver County, Pennsylvania
